{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T14:57:26.671Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dynamic Programming (DP)"},{"type":"text","text":" is an algorithmic technique that solves complex problems by breaking them into "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"smaller overlapping subproblems"},{"type":"text","text":", solving each subproblem "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"only once"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"storing the results"},{"type":"text","text":" (memoization) to avoid redundant computation. DP optimizes plain recursion by trading time for space, reducing exponential time complexity (e.g., O(2ⁿ)) to polynomial complexity (e.g., O(n²)). In Gen AI, DP is essential for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"sequence alignment"},{"type":"text","text":" (Longest Common Subsequence for text similarity), "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"edit distance"},{"type":"text","text":" (spell checking, version control), "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"optimal measurement planning"},{"type":"text","text":" (autonomous robots), and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"auto-formulating DP problems"},{"type":"text","text":" with LLMs (DP-Bench, DPLM)."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Definition"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Purpose"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core Idea"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Break into overlapping subproblems, store results"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Avoid redundant computation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Overlapping Subproblems"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subproblems repeat (same inputs)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"DP-worthy (vs. divide-and-conquer)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Optimal Substructure"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Optimal solution = optimal sub-solutions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build optimal from sub-optimal"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Memoization"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Store subproblem results (cache)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(1) lookup vs. re-computation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tabulation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fill DP table iteratively (bottom-up)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Avoid recursion overhead"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters for Gen AI"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ❌ WITHOUT DP: Exponential recursion (very slow)\n# Fibonacci: O(2ⁿ) = 2⁵⁰ ≈ 1 quadrillion calls for n=50\ndef fibonacci_slow(n):\n    if n <= 1:\n        return n\n    return fibonacci_slow(n - 1) + fibonacci_slow(n - 2)  # ❌ O(2ⁿ) [web:209]\n\nfibonacci_slow(50)  # ❌ 1 quadrillion calls (hours to compute) [web:209]\n\n# ✅ WITH DP: Linear time (fast)\n# Top-Down DP (Memoization): O(n)\ndef fibonacci_memo(n, memo={}):\n    if n in memo:  # ✅ Cached result\n        return memo[n]\n    if n <= 1:  # ✅ Base case\n        return n\n    memo[n] = fibonacci_memo(n - 1, memo) + fibonacci_memo(n - 2, memo)  # ✅ Store\n    return memo[n]  # ✅ O(n) [web:209]\n\nfibonacci_memo(50)  # ✅ 50 calls (instant) [web:209]\n\n# Bottom-Up DP (Tabulation): O(n)\ndef fibonacci_tab(n):\n    if n <= 1:\n        return n\n    dp = [0] * (n + 1)  # ✅ DP table\n    dp [archconf](https://archconf.com/session?id=53260) = 1\n    for i in range(2, n + 1):  # ✅ Fill table\n        dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + dp[i - 2]\n    return dp[n]  # ✅ O(n) [web:209]\n\nfibonacci_tab(50)  # ✅ 50 iterations (instant) [web:209]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exponential → Polynomial"},{"type":"text","text":": O(2ⁿ) → O(n²) for many problems\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sequence alignment"},{"type":"text","text":": LCS for text similarity, NLP, genetic sequencing\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Edit distance"},{"type":"text","text":": Spell checking, version control (diff utility)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Optimal planning"},{"type":"text","text":": Autonomous robots, measurement sequences\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auto DP formulation"},{"type":"text","text":": LLMs generate DP recurrences (DPLM, DP-Bench)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Dynamic Programming Works (Core Steps) ⭐"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Identify DP-Worthy Problem"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Problem must have:\n# 1. Overlapping subproblems (same inputs repeat) [web:208][web:209]\n# 2. Optimal substructure (optimal = optimal sub-solutions) [web:208][web:209]\n\n# ✅ DP-worthy:\n# - Fibonacci:fib(n-1), fib(n-2) repeat [web:209]\n# - LCS: LCS(i-1, j-1) repeats [web:208][web:211]\n# - Knapsack: knapsack(i-1, w) repeats [web:208]\n\n# ❌ NOT DP-worthy (divide-and-conquer):\n# - Merge Sort: subproblems don't overlap [web:208]\n# - Binary Search: subproblems don't overlap [web:208]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define State"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ State = variables that describe problem state\n# Example: LCS (Longest Common Subsequence)\n# State: dp[i][j] = length of LCS for text1[0:i] and text2[0:j] [web:208][web:211]\n\ntext1 = \"ABCBDAB\"\ntext2 = \"BDCABA\"\n\n# dp[i][j]: LCS length for text1[:i] and text2[:j]\n# i = 0..len(text1), j = 0..len(text2) [web:208][web:211]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define Transition (Recurrence)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Transition: How to compute dp[i] from previous states\n# Example: LCS recurrence [web:208][web:211]\n\ndef lcs(text1, text2):\n    n, m = len(text1), len(text2)\n    dp = [[0] * (m + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]  # ✅ DP table [web:208][web:211]\n    \n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\n        for j in range(1, m + 1):\n            if text1[i - 1] == text2[j - 1]:  # ✅ Match\n                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1  # ✅ +1 to LCS [web:208][web:211]\n            else:  # ✅ Mismatch\n                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1])  # ✅ Max of two [web:208][web:211]\n    \n    return dp[n][m]  # ✅ LCS length [web:208][web:211]\n\nlcs(\"ABCBDAB\", \"BDCABA\")  # ✅ 4 (LCS: \"BDAB\" or \"BCAB\") [web:208][web:211]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Initialize DP Table"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Initialize base cases\n# Example: Fibonacci\ndp = [0] * (n + 1)  # ✅ DP table\ndp[0] = 0  # ✅ Base case\ndp [archconf](https://archconf.com/session?id=53260) = 1  # ✅ Base case [web:209]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fill DP Table"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Fill table iteratively (bottom-up)\n# Example: Fibonacci\nfor i in range(2, n + 1):  # ✅ Loop from 2 to n\n    dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + dp[i - 2]  # ✅ Transition [web:209]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Extract Solution"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Solution stored in DP table\n# Example: Fibonacci\nreturn dp[n]  # ✅ nth Fibonacci number [web:209]\n\n# Example: LCS\nreturn dp[n][m]  # ✅ LCS length [web:208][web:211]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two DP Approaches ⭐"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Approach"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Top-Down (Memoization)"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bottom-Up (Tabulation)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Direction"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start with original problem, recurse"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start with base cases, iterate up"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Implementation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Recursion + cache"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Loop + DP table"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Code Style"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Easier to write (natural recursion)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"More efficient (no recursion overhead)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Space"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(d) where d = recursion depth"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n) where n = table size"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Case"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex state, hard to order"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple state, easy to order"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common DP Algorithms ⭐"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Longest Common Subsequence (LCS)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ LCS: Sequence alignment (NLP, genetic sequencing, version control) [web:208][web:211]\ndef lcs(text1, text2):\n    n, m = len(text1), len(text2)\n    dp = [[0] * (m + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]\n    \n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\n        for j in range(1, m + 1):\n            if text1[i - 1] == text2[j - 1]:\n                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1\n            else:\n                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1])\n    \n    return dp[n][m]  # ✅ LCS length [web:208][web:211]\n\nlcs(\"ABCBDAB\", \"BDCABA\")  # ✅ 4 (LCS: \"BDAB\") [web:208][web:211]\n# Time: O(n × m), Space: O(n × m) [web:208][web:211]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Edit Distance (Levenshtein Distance)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Edit Distance: Spell checking, version control (diff utility) [web:208][web:212]\ndef edit_distance(word1, word2):\n    n, m = len(word1), len(word2)\n    dp = [[0] * (m + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]\n    \n    # Initialize base cases\n    for i in range(n + 1):\n        dp[i][0] = i  # ✅ Delete all\n    for j in range(m + 1):\n        dp[0][j] = j  # ✅ Insert all\n    \n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\n        for j in range(1, m + 1):\n            if word1[i - 1] == word2[j - 1]:\n                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1]  # ✅ No operation\n            else:\n                dp[i][j] = 1 + min(\n                    dp[i - 1][j],  # ✅ Delete\n                    dp[i][j - 1],  # ✅ Insert\n                    dp[i - 1][j - 1]  # ✅ Replace\n                )\n    \n    return dp[n][m]  # ✅ Edit distance [web:208][web:212]\n\nedit_distance(\"kitten\", \"sitting\")  # ✅ 3 (k→s, e→i, insert g) [web:208][web:212]\n# Time: O(n × m), Space: O(n × m) [web:208][web:212]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"0/1 Knapsack"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ 0/1 Knapsack: Greedy fails, DP works [web:208]\n# items: (weight, value), capacity: max weight\ndef knapsack(items, capacity):\n    n = len(items)\n    dp = [[0] * (capacity + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]\n    \n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\n        weight, value = items[i - 1]\n        for w in range(capacity + 1):\n            dp[i][w] = dp[i - 1][w]  # ✅ Don't include\n            if w >= weight:\n                dp[i][w] = max(dp[i][w], dp[i - 1][w - weight] + value)  # ✅ Include [web:208]\n    \n    return dp[n][capacity]  # ✅ Max value [web:208]\n\nitems = [(10, 60), (20, 100), (30, 120)]  # (weight, value)\nknapsack(items, 50)  # ✅ 220 (items 1 + 2: weight 10+20=30, value 60+100=160... wait, actually 220) [web:208]\n# Time: O(n × capacity), Space: O(n × capacity) [web:208]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Coin Change (Minimum Coins)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Coin Change: Greedy fails for non-canonical coins, DP works [web:208]\ndef coin_change(coins, amount):\n    dp = [amount + 1] * (amount + 1)  # ✅ Initialize with max\n    dp[0] = 0  # ✅ Base case\n    \n    for coin in coins:\n        for a in range(coin, amount + 1):\n            dp[a] = min(dp[a], dp[a - coin] + 1)  # ✅ Min coins [web:208]\n    \n    return dp[amount] if dp[amount] <= amount else -1  # ✅ Result [web:208]\n\ncoin_change([1, 2, 5], 11)  # ✅ 3 (5 + 5 + 1) [web:208]\n# Time: O(n × amount), Space: O(amount) [web:208]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ LIS: O(n²) DP vs O(n log n) patience method [web:208]\ndef lis(nums):\n    if not nums:\n        return 0\n    \n    dp =  [archconf](https://archconf.com/session?id=53260) * len(nums)  # ✅ Each element is LIS of length 1\n    \n    for i in range(1, len(nums)):\n        for j in range(i):\n            if nums[j] < nums[i]:\n                dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1)  # ✅ Extend LIS [web:208]\n    \n    return max(dp)  # ✅ Longest LIS [web:208]\n\nlis([10, 9, 2, 5, 3, 7, 101, 18])  # ✅ 4 ([2, 3, 7, 101] or [2, 5, 7, 18]) [web:208]\n# Time: O(n²), Space: O(n) [web:208]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Time Complexity Comparison"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Brute Force"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"DP (Memoization)"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"DP (Tabulation)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fibonacci"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(2ⁿ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LCS"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(2ⁿ⁺ᵐ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × m)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × m)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Edit Distance"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(3ⁿ⁺ᵐ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × m)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × m)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"0/1 Knapsack"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(2ⁿ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × capacity)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × capacity)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Coin Change"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(amountⁿ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × amount)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O(n × amount)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Gen AI Applications ⭐"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sequence Alignment (NLP, Genetic Sequencing)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ LCS for text similarity (NLP, sentiment analysis, version control) [web:208][web:211]\n# Essential for: text similarity analysis, genetic sequencing, version control [web:211]\n\ndef text_similarity(text1, text2):\n    lcs_length = lcs(text1, text2)  # ✅ O(n × m) [web:208][web:211]\n    return lcs_length / max(len(text1), len(text2))  # ✅ Similarity score [web:211]\n\ntext_similarity(\"I love AI\", \"I love machine learning\")  # ✅ 0.5 (LCS: \"I love \") [web:211]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Spell Checking (Edit Distance)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Edit distance for spell checking (find closest word) [web:208][web:212]\ndef spell_check(word, dictionary):\n    best_word = None\n    best_distance = float('inf')\n    \n    for dict_word in dictionary:\n        distance = edit_distance(word, dict_word)  # ✅ O(n × m) [web:208][web:212]\n        if distance < best_distance:\n            best_distance = distance\n            best_word = dict_word\n    \n    return best_word  # ✅ Closest word [web:208][web:212]\n\nspell_check(\"kitten\", [\"sitting\", \"cat\", \"dog\"])  # ✅ \"sitting\" (distance 3) [web:208][web:212]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Optimal Measurement Planning (Autonomous Robots)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ DP for optimal sequence of informative measurements (autonomous agents) [web:210]\n# Reduces measurements by ~50% compared to greedy approaches [web:210]\n\ndef optimal_measurement_plan(states, measurements):\n    # DP: Sequentially maximize entropy of measurement outcomes [web:210]\n    dp = [[0] * len(measurements) for _ in range(len(states))]\n    \n    for i in range(len(states)):\n        for j in range(len(measurements)):\n            # DP transition: maximize entropy [web:210]\n            dp[i][j] = max_entropy(states[i], measurements[j]) + dp[i - 1][j - 1]\n    \n    return dp[-1][-1]  # ✅ Optimal plan [web:210]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auto-Formulating DP with LLMs"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ LLMs auto-generate DP recurrences (DP-Bench, DPLM) [web:213]\n# DPLM: 7B-parameter model, comparable to o1 and DeepSeek-R1 [web:213]\n\n# DP-Bench: First benchmark for textbook-level DP problems [web:213]\n# DualReflect: Synthetic data generation (forward + backward) [web:213]\n\ndef auto_formulate_dp(problem):\n    # LLM generates DP recurrence [web:213]\n    recurrence = llm_generate_recurrence(problem)  # ✅ Auto-formulate [web:213]\n    return recurrence  # ✅ DP solution [web:213]\n\nauto_formulate_dp(\"Find longest path in DAG\")  # ✅ LLM generates DP recurrence [web:213]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use (Decision Criteria)"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use DP"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Greedy"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Brute Force"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Overlapping subproblems"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Fibonacci, LCS, Knapsack"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ No overlap"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ Too slow"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Greedy property holds"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"⚠️ Works but overkill"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Fractional knapsack, Dijkstra"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"ro